caption: Some folks on here have called this place "the Chipotle for Mediterranean food" and that's pretty spot on. Very customizable options and they're all tasty!

If you like Mediterranean food this is a great spot to grab a good lunch. We were visiting Chicago and due to my daughters food allergies, she found this place on her app. We all loved it. Food is very tasty, the service was fast, the place was clean, just good all around. A bit cramped during the lunch rush, but still okay. You go through a line and pick each of the items you want so you can see exactly what you are getting. Loved it so much we returned a few days later.

This is a good place for Mediterranean food. Their plates are great and their red hot sauce is one of the best I've had. It's full of flavor, not just pure heat. The reason for four stars? Every single time I order a chicken wrap, they give it to me with "structural integrity" issues. Not once, not twice but almost every time, the wrap breaks in the middle. They managed to perfect the lamb meet all wrap, but this one they still need to work on. However, all in all, a great place to eat with lots of seating. But be prepared to stay in line during lunch rush. To skip that, order online on their site or use ritual app, cause they're on it as well.

That was a bit surprising as I was still far from him and I said I am new here and let me check the menu options and I decided to go with falafal rice bowl.  He transferred the bowl with Rice and Falafal to next gentleman and he asked me what kind of sauces I will have in my bowl. I said let me reach there first and will let you know.... He kept staring at me as if I am the one who is delaying.... I mean, how can you ask what to put in your bowl even when I do not the what kind of sauces they have and is not visible from where you are standing far. Roti is conveniently located near the Sears Tower, making this a great lunch spot for a tourist in the loop or a worker looking to grab a quick, cheap (based on the standards of the loop), and delicious lunch. Roti is set up like a Chipotle, meaning that you choose your base (rice, salad, pita), meat, and then corresponding sauces and toppings. If you're unfamiliar with Mediterranean food, don't hesitate to ask questions about the sauces and toppings as the friendly staff is more than happy to supply the answer. Once you reach the front of the line your food is assembled and packed up for you to go within a matter of minutes. I highly recommend the chicken roti salad with the red pepper sauce, it's a tried and true combination!

Roti is the quick service restaurant (QSR) Mediterranean answer to Chipotle's Mexican QSR. Prices are similar, service is similar, and 'feels' similar. Except for the food. I really like the flavor of everything they got. If you want something quick, flavorful, and reasonably priced, I'd recommend going here.
